In her remarks at the "Passing the Baton" conference, National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice discussed the challenges and accomplishments of the Obama administration in the field of national security. She highlighted the importance of focusing on both immediate challenges and long-term strategic goals. Rice mentioned the economic progress made during Obama's presidency, as well as the winding down of wars in Iraq and Afghanistan. She also discussed the nuclear deal with Iran, the fight against terrorism, the rebalancing towards the Asia-Pacific region, and the importance of upholding the international order. Rice emphasized the need to protect American values and alliances while addressing diverse threats. She also mentioned the smooth transition of power to the incoming administration. Rice expressed her pride in the National Security Council staff and offered her support to General Mike Flynn, her successor. In conclusion, she reflected on the opportunities provided by the United States and expressed confidence in the future of the country.